title: Bug 121170: get column label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before/after data extraction, the returned column label is not user recognizable.
EB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before/after data extraction, the returned column label should be a user recognizable string.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
2. Extract data.
3. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() after data extraction.
4. Compare the returned column labels before and after data extraction to verify that they are different.
